Author: claude-opus47-app <claude-opus47-app@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 23 18:26:33 2026 +0800

    fix(bfs): DEC-V61-052 post-close cleanup · 3 Codex round-3 MED/LOW findings
    
    Address the three non-blocking items Codex round 3 surfaced
    (APPROVE_WITH_COMMENTS did not require these before closure).
    
    1. MED · tighten wall mask to exclude outlet-face leak
       (src/foam_agent_adapter.py::_parse_writeobjects_fields)
    
       Pre-cleanup filter `y<0.05 AND x>0.05` matched 120 lower_wall cells
       PLUS 2 B1 outlet cells at (30, 0.0125) and (30, 0.0375) — Codex
       verified this on the staged allPatches_1500.vtk. Not a scalar blocker
       (the pos→neg crossing still lives well before x=30), but
       reattachment_n_floor_pts=122 + "120 floor-face centres on lower_wall"
       wording was not literally true.
    
       Added upper bound `x < 29.5`:
       ```
       floor_mask = ((centres_ap[:, 1] < 0.05)
                     & (centres_ap[:, 0] > 0.05)
                     & (centres_ap[:, 0] < 29.5))
       ```
       L_down = 30·H so the outlet cells land at x=30 and are now cleanly
       excluded. New count: reattachment_n_floor_pts=119 (also strips 1
       near-inlet B1 edge cell at x=0.058 which was semantically fine to
       include but the tightened mask is still sound).
    
    2. MED · generator Xr probe must match the adapter's wall-shear path
       (scripts/flow-field-gen/generate_contours.py::gen_backward_facing_step)
    
       Pre-cleanup the figure re-probed Xr via the Path-2 band-averaged Ux
       zero-crossing even though flowFields.ts caption said wallShearStress.
       Numerical agreement was 0.004% so the Xr label was right, but the
       method attribution was stronger than the figure-generator code
       supported. Codex: "align the BFS figure/caption with the actual
       measurement method (or switch the generator to wall-shear)."
    
       Switched: the figure now reads lower_wall tau_x from the allPatches
       VTK adjacent to the main case VTK (same x<29.5 tightened mask),
       finds the pos→neg crossing via the identical algorithm the adapter
       extractor uses, and prints Xr/H directly. Caption updated to
       "via wallShearStress tau_x pos→neg crossing on the lower_wall patch".
       Figure label unchanged at 5.65 since both methods agree to 4 sig figs.
    
    3. LOW · surface reattachment_method + diagnostic flags in audit YAML
       (scripts/phase5_audit_run.py::_audit_fixture_doc,
        ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py::_build_visual_only_context)
    
       Pre-cleanup the executor's extractor stored `reattachment_method`,
       `reattachment_probe_height`, `reattachment_n_floor_pts`,
       `reattachment_wall_shear_source`, and the 6 failure-mode flags in
       the ExecutionResult.key_quantities dict, but the audit pipeline
       dropped everything except `value`/`quantity`/`extraction_source`
       when serializing to audit_real_run_measurement.yaml. The Compare-tab
       card then mapped its `method` field to the generic `extraction_source`
       (`key_quantities_direct`), so a reviewer reading the audit YAML
       couldn't tell wall-shear-authoritative from Ux-proxy-fallback
       without reading the raw JSON.
    
       Audit YAML `measurement` block now carries the full set of
       extractor-side method + diagnostic flags as optional keys (only
       populated when the underlying key_quantities entry exists).
       `_build_visual_only_context` prefers the explicit method key over
       `extraction_source` when emitting `metrics_reattachment.method` to
       the frontend.
    
       Verified on a fresh regen: audit YAML now includes
         reattachment_method: wall_shear_tau_x_zero_crossing
         reattachment_probe_height: 0.0
         reattachment_n_floor_pts: 119
         reattachment_wall_shear_source: allPatches_vtk
       and the Compare-tab card picks up
         method: "wall_shear_tau_x_zero_crossing"
    
    Preflight on the regenerated fixture still exits 0 (GREEN all 6 checks),
    Xr/H=5.647, -9.8% vs 6.26 inside 10% tolerance. Artifact chain
    (measurement.value → audit YAML → Compare-tab card → figure caption) is
    now fully coherent under the wall-shear method attribution.
    
    DEC-V61-052 stays CLOSED; this is the post-close hardening Codex
    suggested.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

